tLUNhcGl0YWw/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBa39d9db0" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" item=
scope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decorat=
ion: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #00000=
0; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;"> Coliseum and Purpl=
e settled the lawsuit</a>. The <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusine=
ss.com/click/31207070.258446/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYnVzaW5lc3N3aXJlLmNvbS9uZXdzL2=
hvbWUvMjAyMzA0MTMwMDU4MDcvZW4vUHVycGxlLUlubm92YXRpb24tQW5ub3VuY2VzLUNvb3Blc=
mF0aXZlLUZyYW1ld29yay13aXRoLUNvbGlzZXVtLUNhcGl0YWw/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23c=
Ca39d9db0" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank"=
 style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-w=
idth: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; backgr=
ound-color: #ccc;"> terms of the settlement</a> include:=E2=80=8B=E2=80=8B=
=E2=80=8B=E2=80=8B=E2=80=8B=E2=80=8B</p>
<ul style=3D"list-style-type: disc; padding-left: 40px; margin: 16px 0;">=
=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">The board will have eight members, fou=
r from Coliseum=E2=80=99s slate, three from the existing non-Coliseum direc=
tors and one new member.</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">Coliseum=
=E2=80=99s managing partner becomes chairman of the board; the previous cha=
irman of the board will resign.</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">Co=
liseum will vote for the agreed nominees in 2023 and 2024.</li>=09<li style=
=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">The board will terminate its special committee and=
 its poison pill, and promise not to do another poison pill without Coliseu=
m=E2=80=99s consent.</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">The board wil=
l get rid of the PRPLS and never do them again.</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-=
bottom: 5px;">Purple will pay Coliseum up to $4 million to reimburse it for=
 the costs of suing over the PRPLS.</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;=
">They drop the lawsuit.</li>
</ul>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">It=E2=80=99s a bit of a mixed bag: The old boa=
rd does get to keep four board seats through 2024, but it has given up its =
ability to block Coliseum=E2=80=99s actions with weird preferred stock or a=
 poison pill.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">When we first talked about the PRPLS, <a href=
=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/31207070.258446/aHR0cHM6L=
y93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjMtMDItMTUvcHVycGxlLWlu=
bm92YXRpb24tcy1wcnBscy1pbm5vdmF0aW9uP2NtcGlkPUJCRDA0MTgyM19NT05FWVNUVUZGJnV=
0bV9tZWRpdW09ZW1haWwmdXRtX3NvdXJjZT1uZXdzbGV0dGVyJnV0bV90ZXJtPTIzMDQxOCZ1dG=
1fY2FtcGFpZ249bW9uZXlzdHVmZg/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cC29187599" itemprop=3D=
"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #0000=
00; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bott=
om-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">  I=
 wrote that</a> we =E2=80=9Clive in a golden age of blank-check preferred s=
tock with weird voting rights and fun acronyms.=E2=80=9D Starting with the =
APEs, boards decided that they could shape shareholding voting in ways that=
 they wanted. But I think that golden age is ending? Boards saw the opportu=
nity to take a bit more power by adjusting shareholder voting rights, but t=
hey kept getting sued, and they seem to have backed away from it.=C2=A0</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Incidentally the poison pill is <em>also </em>=
a weird blank-check preferred stock designed to keep the board in power ove=
r shareholder objections. We <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness=
.com/click/31207070.258446/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2Fy=
dGljbGVzLzIwMjItMDQtMTgvdHdpdHRlci1oYXMtYS1wb2lzb24tcGlsbC1ub3c_Y21waWQ9QkJ=
EMDQxODIzX01PTkVZU1RVRkYmdXRtX21lZGl1bT1lbWFpbCZ1dG1fc291cmNlPW5ld3NsZXR0ZX=
ImdXRtX3Rlcm09MjMwNDE4JnV0bV9jYW1wYWlnbj1tb25leXN0dWZm/607f07ceef4b8524a319=
a23cB09e63944" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_bl=
ank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bott=
om-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; ba=
ckground-color: #ccc;"> talked about poison pills in detail</a> back when T=
witter Inc. did one, but the main idea of the poison pill is that if some a=
cquirer wants to buy a majority of the company=E2=80=99s stock =E2=80=94=C2=
=A0in a tender offer, or in the open market =E2=80=94=C2=A0the board can bl=
ock it with =E2=80=9Cshareholder rights plan=E2=80=9D that issues zillions =
of shares to everyone <em>other</em> than the acquirer, diluting the acquir=
er; the effect is to prevent the acquirer from buying stock from shareholde=
rs who want to sell it. That=E2=80=99s weird! And Delaware courts have, for=
 decades, allowed it: Yes, the pill lets directors basically overrule share=
holders=E2=80=99 desires (to sell the company), but if the directors use it=
 in good faith =E2=80=94=C2=A0if they use a pill to prevent a real =E2=80=
=9Cthreat=E2=80=9D to the company, like a takeover offer that they think is=
 too low =E2=80=94=C2=A0then they=E2=80=99re mostly allowed to use it. In s=
ome sense APEs and PRPLS and the rest are an extension of that idea, that b=
oards of directors can use blank-check preferred stock to maintain control =
of their companies even when shareholders are being difficult. But they mig=
ht have extended the idea too far.</p>
